{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"@"},{"kind":"attribute","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM","text":"MainActor"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"OUDSButton","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"mentions","mentions":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Layouts","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Actions"]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Appearances","anchor":"Appearances","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Five appearances are proposed for all layouts:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"default (by default)","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Default buttons are used for actions which are not mandatory or essential for the user."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"strong"}]},{"text":": Should be singular and prominent, limited to one per view.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It should be reserved for the most critical action, such as “Next,” “Save,” “Submit,” etc. It is a “call for action”.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"brand"}]},{"type":"text","text":": A brand primary color alternative to the "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"strong"}]},{"type":"text","text":" button."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"To be used sparingly for high-value specific actions or to visually anchor a brand moment. Do not use it as the default primary button in your interfaces."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"A button with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSButton.Appearance.Brand"},{"text":" appearance is not allowed as a direct or indirect child of an ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSColoredSurface"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"minimal"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": Minimal buttons are commonly used for actions that are considered less crucial. They can be used independently or together with a strong button.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"negative"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Negative buttons should be used sparingly to warn of a destructive action,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for example, delete or remove, typically resulting in the opening of a confirmation dialog."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"A button with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSButton.Appearance.Negative"},{"type":"text","text":" appearance is not allowed as a direct or indirect child of an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSColoredSurface"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"level":2,"anchor":"Code-samples","type":"heading","text":"Code samples"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["    \/\/ Icon only with default appearance","    OUDSButton(icon: Image(\"ic_heart\"), accessibilityLabel: \"Like\", appearance: .default) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","    \/\/ Or simpler","    OUDSButton(icon: Image(\"ic_heart\"), accessibilityLabel: \"Like\") { \/* the action to process *\/ }","","    \/\/ Text only with negative appearance","    OUDSButton(text: \"Delete\", appearance: .negative,  style: .default) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","    \/\/ Or simpler","    OUDSButton(text: \"Delete\", appearance: .negative) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","","    \/\/ A loading button","    OUDSButton(text: \"Delete\", style: .loading) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","","    \/\/ Text and icon with strong appearance","    OUDSButton(text: \"Validate\", icon: Image(\"ic_heart\"), appearance: .strong) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","","    \/\/ Text and icon with strong appearance and button taking full width","    OUDSButton(text: \"Validate\", icon: Image(\"ic_heart\"), appearance: .strong, isFullWidth: true) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","","    \/\/ Localizable from bundle can also be used","    OUDSButton(LocalizedStringKey(\"validate_button\"), bundle: Bundle.module, appearance: .strong) { }"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you need to flip your icon depending to the layout direction or not (e.g. if RTL mode lose semantics  \/ meanings):"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["    @Environment(\\.layoutDirection) var layoutDirection","","    OUDSButton(text: \"Button\",","               icon: Image(systemName: \"figure.handball\"),","               flipIcon: layoutDirection == .rightToLeft)"]},{"level":2,"anchor":"Styles","type":"heading","text":"Styles"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Two style are available:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"default (by default)"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": used in the normal usage of button. The aspect of the button changes for  states "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"disabled"}]},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"pressed"}]},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"hovered"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" or normal (i.e. "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"enabled"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":")"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"loading"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": used after button was clicked and probably data are requested before navigate to a next screen or get updated data."}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Rounded layout","anchor":"Rounded-layout"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Buttons can have rounded layouts to be favored in more emotional, immersive contexts or those tied to specific visual identities."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For standard or business-oriented journeys, keep the default corners."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This evolution addresses the need for flexibility in adapting the design to some brand contexts."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To activate the rounded button behavior, set to true the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hasRoundedButtons"},{"type":"text","text":" values of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Tuning"},{"type":"text","text":" object"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in your theme configuration (if the theme exposes this property at init)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Some themes do not have this flexibility like "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SoshTheme"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"WireframeTheme","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Colored surface","anchor":"Colored-surface"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If button is placed on colored surface using ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSColoredSurface"},{"text":", the default colors (content, background and border) are automatically adjusted to switch to monochrome mode.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Remark: Today it is not allowed to place a Negative nor a Brand button on a colored surface.","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"}]},{"anchor":"Specific-behavior","text":"Specific behavior","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For accessibility reasons, if the system settings for reducing motion is enabled, the loading indicator does not move."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For ecodesign reasons, if the device is in low power mode, the loading indicator does not move."}]},{"anchor":"Design-documentation","text":"Design documentation","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"https:\/\/r.orange.fr\/r\/S-ouds-doc-button","type":"reference","isActive":true}]},{"anchor":"Themes-rendering","text":"Themes rendering","type":"heading","level":2},{"anchor":"Orange","text":"Orange","type":"heading","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_button_Orange","type":"image"}]},{"anchor":"Orange-Compact","text":"Orange Compact","type":"heading","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_button_OrangeCompact"}]},{"anchor":"Sosh","text":"Sosh","type":"heading","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_button_Sosh"}]},{"anchor":"Wireframe","text":"Wireframe","type":"heading","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_button_Wireframe"}]},{"name":"Version","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"3.2.0 (Figma component design version)","type":"text"}]}],"type":"aside","style":"note"},{"name":"Since","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"0.10.0","type":"text"}]}],"type":"aside","style":"note"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents"]]},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Structure","platforms":[{"beta":false,"name":"iOS","deprecated":false,"introducedAt":"15.0","unavailable":false},{"beta":false,"name":"macOS","deprecated":false,"introducedAt":"13.0","unavailable":false},{"introducedAt":"16.0","name":"tvOS","deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"beta":false},{"introducedAt":"1.0","name":"visionOS","deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"beta":fa